<translate>

FrameForge is dedicated to creating Frames and Beams, and apply operations (miter cuts, trim cuts) to theses profiles.

== Create the skeleton ==

Beams are mapped onto Edges or ParametricLine (from a Sketch for instance). For a start, we are going to create a simple frame.

</translate>
<ol>
<li>
<translate>
In a new file, switch to the FrameForge workbench.
</translate>
</li>
<li>
<translate>
Create a sketch, and select orientation (XY for instance).
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_00-create-sketch.png|Create Sketch]]
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_01-select-orientation.png|Select Orientation]]
</translate>
</li>
<li>
<translate>
Draw a simple square in the sketch… it will be our skeleton
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_02-create-frame-skeleton.png|Create Skeleton]]
</translate>
</li>
<li>
<translate>
Close the Sketch edit mode.
</translate>
</li>
</ol>
<translate>

== Create the frame ==

</translate>
<ol>
<li>
<translate>
Lauch the Profile tool.
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_10-profiles.png|profile]]
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_10-profiles-task.png|profile]]
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_10-profiles-task-2.png|profile]]
</translate>
</li>
<li>
<translate>
Select a profile from the lists (Material / Family / Size)
<br>
You can change the size just below the family, the tool has a lot of predefined profile, you can also change the parameters…
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_11-profiles-family.png|profiles choice]]
</translate>
</li>
<li>
<translate>
In the 3D View, select edges to apply the profile creation.
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_13-edge-selection.png|Edge Selection]]
</translate>
</li>
<li>
<translate>
And press OK in the Create Profile Task. Now, you have four profiles !
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_14-profiles-done.png|Profiles]]
<br>
[[Image:FrameForge_14-zoom-on-profiles.png|Zoom in profile]]
</translate>
</li>
